201
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,640
-I'll beat you up.
-Professor Zan!

202
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,500
Professor Zan!

203
00:12:03,330 --> 00:12:03,970
Young man,

204
00:12:03,970 --> 00:12:06,090
could you tell me
if Professor Zan is here?

205
00:12:06,090 --> 00:12:06,970
Mr. Zan

206
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:08,580
went to Beijing for a seminar.

207
00:12:08,580 --> 00:12:09,400
He just left this afternoon.

208
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,460
He went to Beijing?

209
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:15,210
But you need to provide evidence as to

210
00:12:15,210 --> 00:12:18,010
why these six items are claimed

211
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:19,730
to be from China.

212
00:12:19,730 --> 00:12:20,160
Sir.

213
00:12:21,410 --> 00:12:22,770
Your auction house

214
00:12:23,970 --> 00:12:28,610
clearly stated in the item
description that

215
00:12:28,730 --> 00:12:33,010
those six black pottery
figurines are from China.

216
00:12:33,450 --> 00:12:34,310
From Qinchuan.

217
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,400
What more do I need to say?

218
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:39,760
We did mention the word China.

219
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:44,240
But that doesn't mean that
they automatically belong to you.

220
00:12:44,850 --> 00:12:48,490
By your logic, does it mean that
you can claim ownership

221
00:12:48,490 --> 00:12:51,210
of any items in our auction
related to China?

222
00:12:51,290 --> 00:12:53,340
Blue and White Ruyi Vase,

223
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:56,430
which is dated back to
Qianlong Period of Qing Dynasty.

224
00:12:56,690 --> 00:12:59,040
The shape, the decorative patterns,
and the inscriptions

225
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,040
showcase

226
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,370
the exquisite craftsmanship

227
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:05,450
and its cultural heritage of porcelain
production in Qing Dynasty.

228
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:06,730
Hello.

229
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,370
Could you please tell me

230
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:09,500
